page.title: List of International Space Station visitors

revisions.rev:
This is a '''list of visitors to the [[International Space Station]]''' in alphabetical order. Station crew names are in '''bold'''. The suffix ''(twice, thrice, ...)'' refers to the individual's number of ISS visits, not his or her total number of space flights. Entries without a flag symbol indicate that the person was an American citizen at launch. Entries without a female symbol ([[Image:Symbol venus.svg|10px]]) are men. == Statistics == [[File:ISS Visitors.svg|right|300px]] {{As of|2011|11|22|df=US}}, 204 individuals have made 325 visits to the ISS, including the three people currently at the station ([[Expedition 30]]). NASA astronauts [[Mark Kelly (astronaut)|Mark Kelly]] and [[Frederick W. Sturckow]] have visited the ISS four times, while 23 people have visited thrice and 69 people have visited twice. Note that this list assigns individuals with [[dual citizenship]] to their country of primary residence at time of launch (for example, the [[Iran]]ian-[[United States|American]] space tourist [[Anousheh Ansari]] is only listed under the [[United States]]). ===By nationality=== {| class="wikitable" !Nationality !Trips !Fliers !Notes |- | {{flag|United States}} || 235 || 138 || 27 women, 35 ISS crew members, five [[space tourist|tourists]], 55 double, 18 triple and two quadruple flights |- | {{flag|Russia}} || 53 || 37 || 30 ISS crew members, eight double and four triple flights |- | {{flag|Canada}} || 8 || 7 || one woman, one ISS crew member, one double flight, one tourist |- | {{flag|Japan}} || 8 || 6 || one woman, three ISS crew members, two double flights |- | {{flag|Italy}} || 6 || 3 || one ISS crew member, one double and one triple flight |- | {{flag|France}} || 3 || 3 || one woman, one ISS crew member |- | {{flag|Germany}} || 2 || 2 || one ISS crew member |- | {{flag|Belgium}} || 2 || 1 || one ISS crew member, one double flight |- | {{flag|Sweden}} || 2 || 1 || one double flight |- | {{flag|Brazil}} || 1 || 1 || |- | {{flag|Malaysia}} || 1 || 1 || |- | {{flag|Netherlands}} || 1 || 1 || |- | {{flag|South Africa}} || 1 || 1 || one tourist |- | {{flag|South Korea}} || 1 || 1 || one woman |- | {{flag|Spain}} || 1 || 1 || |- | '''Total''' || 325 || 204 || 31 women, 73 ISS crew members, 7 tourists, 69 double, 23 triple and two quadruple flights |- |} ===By agency=== {| class="wikitable" !
